---
import Section from './Section.astro';

const stats = [
  { value: '2,500+', label: 'environments defended' },
  { value: '9', label: 'SIEM & EDR/XDR platforms' },
  { value: '7', label: 'industry certifications' },
];
---

<Section id="about" number="01" eyebrow="About" heading="Defense at scale, learning in public">
  <div class="max-w-2xl space-y-5 text-muted-fg">
    <p>
      By day I'm a Principal Security Analyst at <a href="https://www.criticalstart.com" rel="noopener" class="text-foreground underline decoration-accent/40 underline-offset-4 transition-colors duration-(--duration-fast) hover:text-accent-bright hover:decoration-accent">Critical Start</a>, a 24/7 MDR protecting 2,500+ customer environments. When an alert fires, my job is deciding whether it's noise or an incident: digging through the logs to prove it, and executing remediation on live threats when it's real.
    </p>
    <p>
      The rest of the time I build the tools I wish I had on shift: a detection-as-code pipeline, a URL detonation toolbox, a homelab SOC. Building them is how I learn what's actually happening under the hood, and I document what I find on the <a href="/blog" class="text-foreground underline decoration-accent/40 underline-offset-4 transition-colors duration-(--duration-fast) hover:text-accent-bright hover:decoration-accent">blog</a>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <dl class="mt-14 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3" data-reveal-stagger>
    {
      stats.map((stat) => (
        <div class="flex flex-col-reverse gap-1 rounded-lg border border-line bg-surface/60 p-6 transition-colors duration-(--duration-base) hover:border-accent/40">
          <dt class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-fg">
            {stat.label}
          </dt>
          <dd class="font-heading text-4xl font-black tracking-tight text-accent-bright">
            {stat.value}
          </dd>
        </div>
      ))
    }
  </dl>
</Section>
